											<div style="float: right; margin: 0 0 10px 10px;"><img alt="Sylvia Olsen" src="/images/authors/sylvia-olsen-2.jpg" style="width: 200px;"></img></div>
											<p>We are very excited to be hosting Sylvia Olsen as part of the NorthWords Writers Festival in Fort Smith! She will be at the library for two events on Thursday, one of which is aimed at families.</p>
											<p>More information about these events is below. If you would like to see more about the NorthWords Writers Festival, you can <a href="http://northwordsnwt.ca/" target="_blank" title="NorthWords Writers Festival">visit their website</a>.</p>
											<p><strong>Telling Our Story</strong><br />Join Sylvia Olsen for after school storytelling that the whole family can enjoy. Parents, bring your kids and have some fun!<div style="border-left: 3px solid #bdbdbd; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px; padding-left: 5px; text-align: justify;">at the Mary Kaeser Library<br />4:00 - 5:00 pm</div></p>
											<p><strong>Tale Spinners</strong><br />An Evening of lively stories with Sylvia; Fort Smith's own Jim Green, fresh from a performance at the Northern Scene Festival in Ottawa; and Patti-Kay Hamilton, one of the writers published in the NorthWords Anthology Coming Home. There will be surprising twists and it's up to you to decide what is truth and what is fiction.<div style="border-left: 3px solid #bdbdbd; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px; padding-left: 5px; text-align: justify;">at the Mary Kaeser Library<br />8:00 - 9:30 pm</div></p>
